      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 44 初六</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 44 初六</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>初六：系于金柅，貞吉，有攸往，見凶，羸豕踟躅。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The first SIX, divided, shows how its subject should be kept (like a carriage) tied and fastened to a metal drag, in which case with firm correctness there will be good fortune. (But) if he move in any direction, evil will appear. He will be (like) a lean pig, which is sure to keep jumping about.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
